main event: A radar station in Trenton, Michigan tracked two unidentified flying objects on January 27, 1964.
interesting points: The objects were sighted on radar, moving from west to east at variable speeds.
The report notes conflicting data and descriptions about the objects, making evaluation difficult.
The observer was an experienced telescope user who was unable to track the objects due to their speed.
The objects were sighted at approximately 2:32 AM local time, with the observation lasting around 35 minutes.
The observer reported the sighting to his family but did not see the objects with the naked eye.
sighted object: two unidentified flying objects tracked on radar
photographs: yes, the report indicates photographs were taken
